# Environment Configuration Example

This file shows example environment variables and configurations for different deployment scenarios.

## Development Environment (.env.local or .env.development)

```env
VITE_APP_NAME=MicroSIP Dev
VITE_DEBUG=true
VITE_ENABLE_SIP_TRACE=false
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=localhost
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089
VITE_DEFAULT_TRANSPORT=ws
VITE_DEFAULT_STUN_SERVERS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302
```

## Production Environment (.env.production)

```env
VITE_APP_NAME=MicroSIP
VITE_DEBUG=false
VITE_ENABLE_SIP_TRACE=false
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=your-server.com
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089
VITE_DEFAULT_TRANSPORT=wss
VITE_DEFAULT_STUN_SERVERS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302,stun:stun1.l.google.com:19302
```

## Staging Environment (.env.staging)

```env
VITE_APP_NAME=MicroSIP Staging
VITE_DEBUG=true
VITE_ENABLE_SIP_TRACE=true
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=staging-sip.example.com
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089
VITE_DEFAULT_TRANSPORT=wss
VITE_DEFAULT_STUN_SERVERS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302
```

## Docker Environment

```env
# For docker-compose.yml
SIP_SERVER_HOST=asterisk.local
SIP_SERVER_PORT=8089
SIP_TRANSPORT=wss
APP_PORT=80
SSL_ENABLED=false
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## Kubernetes ConfigMap Example

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: microsip-config
  namespace: default
data:
  VUE_APP_SIP_HOST: "sip.example.com"
  VUE_APP_SIP_PORT: "8089"
  VUE_APP_TRANSPORT: "wss"
  VUE_APP_DEBUG: "false"
```

## AWS Deployment

```env
# Using AWS Cognito for auth
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_COGNITO_POOL_ID=us-east-1_xxxxxxxxx
AWS_COGNITO_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Using AWS S3 for hosting
AWS_S3_BUCKET=my-microsip-app
AWS_CLOUDFRONT_URL=https://d123456.cloudfront.net
```

## Azure Deployment

```env
# Using Azure App Service
AZURE_TENANT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP=microsip-rg
```

## Google Cloud Deployment

```env
GCP_PROJECT_ID=my-project-id
GCP_REGION=us-central1
FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyD...
FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=my-project.firebaseapp.com
```

## Self-Hosted Configuration

```env
# Local network
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=192.168.1.50
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089
VITE_DEFAULT_TRANSPORT=ws
VITE_LOCAL_NETWORK=true

# Or with hostname
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=asterisk.local
VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089
VITE_DEFAULT_TRANSPORT=wss
```

## WebRTC Configuration

```env
# STUN Servers
VITE_STUN_SERVERS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302,stun:stun1.l.google.com:19302

# TURN Server (if needed for symmetric NAT)
VITE_TURN_SERVER=turn:turnserver.example.com:3478
VITE_TURN_USERNAME=turnuser
VITE_TURN_PASSWORD=turnpass

# ICE Transport Policy
VITE_ICE_TRANSPORT_POLICY=all
```

## Logging Configuration

```env
# Log Level: trace, debug, info, warn, error, silent
VITE_LOG_LEVEL=info
VITE_LOG_FORMAT=json
VITE_LOG_FILE=/var/log/microsip/app.log
VITE_LOG_MAX_SIZE=10M
VITE_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS=30
```

## Security Configuration

```env
# CORS
VITE_CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-domain.com
VITE_CORS_CREDENTIALS=true

# CSP Headers
VITE_CSP_ENABLED=true

# Rate Limiting
VITE_RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED=true
VITE_RATE_LIMIT_CALLS_PER_MINUTE=10

# Session
VITE_SESSION_TIMEOUT=3600000
VITE_SESSION_RENEWAL=300000
```

## Feature Flags

```env
# Features
VITE_ENABLE_CALL_RECORDING=false
VITE_ENABLE_CALL_TRANSFER=false
VITE_ENABLE_CONFERENCE=false
VITE_ENABLE_PRESENCE=false
VITE_ENABLE_MESSAGING=false
VITE_ENABLE_VOICEMAIL=false
```

## Analytics & Monitoring

```env
# Sentry Error Tracking
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://xxxxx@sentry.io/12345
VITE_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=production
VITE_SENTRY_TRACE_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1

# Datadog Monitoring
VITE_DD_APPLICATION_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_DD_CLIENT_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_DD_ENVIRONMENT=production

# Custom Analytics
VITE_ANALYTICS_ENABLED=true
VITE_ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT=https://analytics.example.com/v1/events
```

## Proxy Configuration

```env
# If using reverse proxy
VITE_API_PROXY_ENABLED=true
VITE_API_PROXY_TIMEOUT=30000
VITE_WS_PROXY_URL=https://your-domain.com/ws

# Load balancer
VITE_LOAD_BALANCER_ENABLED=true
VITE_LOAD_BALANCER_STICKY_SESSIONS=true
```

## Usage in Vite Config

To use these environment variables in your code:

```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default {
  define: {
    __APP_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(process.env.npm_package_version),
    __BUILD_DATE__: JSON.stringify(new Date().toISOString()),
  },
};
```

In your components:

```javascript
const sipHost = import.meta.env.VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST;
const debug = import.meta.env.VITE_DEBUG === 'true';
const sipPort = import.meta.env.VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT || '8089';
```

## Docker Build

```bash
# Build with environment
docker build \
  --build-arg VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_HOST=asterisk.local \
  --build-arg VITE_DEFAULT_SIP_PORT=8089 \
  -t microsip:latest .
```

---

Configure appropriately for your environment and SIP server setup.
